Russian First-Half Coal Exports Fall on China, Metal Expert Says

-- B y   I l y a   K h r e n n i k o v
-- 
2011-08-16T14:58:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-16/russian-first-half-coal-exports-fall-on-china-metal-expert-says.html
Russia ’s exports of steelmaking coal
fell 21 percent in the first half from a year earlier to 6.86
million metrics tons as  China  cut purchases, according to  Metal
Expert  data.  The data is for washed coal, the Dnipropetrovsk, Ukraine-
based publication reported on its website. China reduced its
imports of Russian steelmaking coal by 77 percent in the period
to 323,000 tons, according to Metal Expert.  Russia’s first-half exports of steam coal, used to fuel
power stations, dropped 10 percent to 40.7 million tons. China,
Turkey and Ukraine slashed steam-coal purchases from the
country, Metal Expert said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ilya Khrennikov in Moscow at 
 ikhrennikov@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
